<br>
Deep within the Mines of Malfunction in Ak'anon,<br>
Stratyxx, the youngest of all the Gnome Plague<br>
Knights of the Dark Reflection, quivered with<br>
fright. She'd had a most dreadful dream, and<br>
the only Gnome, she surmised, who could<br>
possibly analyze it was the wise Mimtia Zethkog.<br>
<br>
Mimtia loved being awakened in the middle of<br>
the night, especially by her favorite new peon,<br>
Stratyxx. Every dream this drudge had seemed<br>
to increase Mimtia's knowledge of the world <br>
beyond Ak'anon. Unfortunately, she had been<br>
bound to the earth of the Mines of Malfunction, <br>
and she couldn't move. The Plague Lord willed it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good morning, my lithe little lowlife! How are<br>
you doing at this midnight hour?&quot; Mimtia smirked. <br>
<br>
&quot;I've had a most terrible dream!&quot; Stratyxx cried. <br>
&quot;The Iksar, of whom I have heard, have come to<br>
me in my sleep, charging headlong into battle!&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Good, good!&quot; Mimtia laughed inwardly at the look<br>
of surprise on the young Plague Knight's face. &quot;I<br>
don't mean it's good that the lizards have visited <br>
you--by no means!--but everything that I hear about<br>
the world of Norrath intrigues me and makes me <br>
wish to hear more about it. Go on, now, slave girl, <br>
reveal your dream!&quot; Mimtia snapped impatiently.<br>
<br>
&quot;As I've said,&quot; replied Stratyxx meekly, &quot;the Iksar<br>
appeared in my dream, six or seven of them, and<br>
they were running purposefully, as if toward a fight!  One<br>
of them was dressed in red and black scale armor,<br>
another in a bright red set of tailored robes, and<br>
still another in green, wielding two powerful Ulaks!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Interesting,&quot; said Mimtia, &quot;but altogether uninformative.<br>
What did these lizard men want, apart from appearing<br>
in a young Gnome's nighttime visions?&quot; she sneered. <br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know!  The Iksar simply wanted to be on their<br>
way, and they seemed not to notice me as I watched<br>
from a distance in my dream. How sleek they were!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Obviously,&quot; Mimtia scoffed, &quot;but what can you tell me<br>
of what these worthless scaled whelps said to you?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know. Seeing as they didn't see me, they said<br>
nothing to me.&quot; Stratyxx stood up and prepared to leave. <br>
<br>
&quot;Don't you go pointing out my logical inconsistencies!&quot; <br>
screamed Mimtia. &quot;Go back to bed, and tomorrow I<br>
want the walls of the Mines of Malfunction scrubbed<br>
with hydrofluoric acid and purified from our plague! <br>
Hold your tongue--you know the drill! I expect you<br>
to have a little more humility in the future, my Stratyxx,<br>
and keep in mind that the Iksar will kill you if you EVER<br>
go to Cabilis!&quot; With a &quot;Hrumph!&quot; of rage, Mimtia fell asleep.<br>
<br>
Stratyxx returned to sleep, waiting for Bertoxxulous to<br>
soothe her mind with shadows, when an Iksar's head,<br>
the Iksar who had been wearing dark green armor and<br>
carrying Ulaks, appeared once again in her mind's eye...<br>
